          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-3 font-medium">Cost to Costco</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-3">Higher (brand premium)</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-3">Lower (direct control)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-3 font-medium">Fan Reception</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-3">Loyal following</td>
            <td class="px-6 py-3">Generally positive; most didn't notice change</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">The Secret to the $1.50 Price</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      Vertical integration is the key. By owning the Kirkland Signature brand and contracting directly with meat processors and bakeries, Costco eliminates the middleman markup that most retailers pay. This margin control is what makes the $1.50 price sustainable — even as labor, energy, and ingredient costs have risen over four decades.
    </p>

